# SESAR CP1 (Common Project 1) - SWIM Deployment

## Overview

**CP1 (Common Project 1)** is the European Union's mandated deployment program for SWIM (System Wide Information Management) infrastructure and services, defined in **EU Regulation 116/2021**. It represents the first phase of the SESAR (Single European Sky ATM Research) deployment program.

## Regulatory Framework

### Single European Sky (SES)

**Objectives**:
- Safety improvement
- Environmental sustainability
- Airspace organization and use optimization
- Interoperability of European ATM network
- Performance-based mechanisms

**SES 2+** enables:
- Cross-border cooperation
- Consolidation of ATM functions
- Reduction of fragmentation
- Standardized information exchange

### EU Regulation 116/2021

**Key Provisions**:
- Definition of Common Projects
- Governance framework
- Implementation timelines
- Stakeholder responsibilities
- Compliance assessment mechanisms

**Mandate**: **2026 implementation deadline** for CP1 services

### EASA Rulemaking

**Role**: European Union Aviation Safety Agency
- Standardization of ATM systems
- Safety regulations
- Equipment certification
- Operational procedures

**Relevant Regulation**: DS.GE (2013/1768) for Extended AMAN and other CP1 functionalities

